    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Relatively small plaques or plates, made of any material and having a devotional image as the subject; often having a loop or pierced holes to allow attachment to a wall or object. Devotional plaques are common in Christian, Hindu, Buddhist, and other religious contexts.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
